"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-06-24-Volunteers-of-past-Olympic-Games-reunite-on-International-Olympic-Day-1uG1s86aHnO-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Each year, June 23 marks International Olympic Day, which was established in 1948 as a global celebration of sports. Ahead of Paris 2024, taking place in July, the Beijing Olympic City Development Association organized a volunteer reunion event on this special occasion at the Beijing Olympic Museum on Sunday.  The volunteers recorded a cheerful greeting video with best wishes for the Paris 2024 Olympics, on June 23, 2024. / Beijing Olympic City Development Association  More than 20 volunteers, including those who have served at past Olympic Games such as Beijing 2008, London 2012, Sochi 2014, Rio 2016, PyeongChang 2018, Tokyo 2020, and Beijing 2022, as well as some who are going to Paris 2024, attended the reunion and shed light on how the volunteering experience had a positive impact on them.  Zhang Wenquan, a volunteer at Beijing 2008 and Beijing 2022, proudly presented his collection of Olympic souvenirs. These impressive collections made him the most popular interviewee for the media during the Games. Among the exhibited items, there was a \\\"Phryges\\\" of the Paris Olympics, a large figure bearing the signature of the president of the Olympic Committee, Thomas Bach.  Each volunteer has a unique story about their journey. Chen Yunzhi applied to volunteer for Rio 2016 at the age of 18 because she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a big fan of the Brazilian soccer team. After staying in Brazil for almost one month, the volunteering experience not only satisfied her curiosity about this South American country but also enhanced her passion for sports and the Olympics. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBeing part of the real Olympics was really like an amplifier for my passion, an amplifier for my enthusiasm. So I followed every single match of the Olympic Games after that,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said.  Qi Huaiyuan, who has volunteered at three Winter Olympic Games, will embark on his journey to Paris this summer. Talking about what makes the experience so special, Qi said, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s about making friends for life. We will stay in touch for years.\\\" Qi volunteered at the PyeongChang 2018 Games and had the opportunity to return to South Korea in February this year, where local volunteers arranged a meeting to catch up. \\\"You make some contributions to society during your stay and you live like a local, which helped me learn about the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s culture. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s something I could not get as a tourist.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Ke Lele will be in Paris at the Eiffel Tower beach volleyball venue to provide event services. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all about love for the Olympics,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said. When he recalled his time at the Rio 2016 Games, the first time he traveled overseas as a young man, he described it as his \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cmost carefree time in life.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d He still can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t forget the time his teammates gave him a ticket to the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball match between China and Serbia. Even though he was still on duty, his manager gave special approval for him to watch the game. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cLele, you did such a great job, you deserve to watch a complete match,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d his manager said at the time.  Chen Shunwen, a student at Peking University, will be one of the volunteers serving at the Paris 2024 Paralympic Games. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have been learning French for two years and I want to apply what I have learned in real life,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she said. She went through a long process to finally get the offer, which made her feel super excited. In preparation for the Paralympic Games, she has been asked to complete the online courses by the Paralympic Games Committee and can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t wait to witness the Chinese team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s victory in the Games.  As a wrap-up of the event, the volunteers recorded a cheerful greeting video with best wishes for the Paris 2024 Olympics. This video will be passed to the Paris Olympics Committee by the volunteers in person next month.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"